<additional><p>Vatican fragment: Georg Zoëga, ed., Catalogus codicum Copticorum manu scriptorum qui in Museo Borgiano velitris adservantur. Rome: Congregatio de Propaganda Fide, 1810, 139, 149–150; Wolf Frederik Engelbreth, ed., Fragmenta Basmurico-Coptica veteris et Novi Testamenti, quae in Museo Borgiano velitris asservantur, cum reliquis versionibus Aegyptiis contulit, Latine vertit, nec non criticis et philologicis adnotationibus. Hauniae: Sebastianus Popp, 1811, xxii, 20–27; Boud’hors, “Réflexions supplémentaires sur les principaux témoins fayoumiques de la Bible.” In Coptica — Gnostica — Manichaica. Mélanges offerts à Wolf-Peter Funk, edited by Paul-Hubert Poirier and Louis Painchaud, 81–108. Bibliothèque copte de Nag Hammadi, «Études» 7. Louvain and Paris: Peeters, 2006, 99–102.</p>
<p>Paris fragments: Anne Boud’hors, “Fragments du Nouveau Testament fayoumique à la Bibliothèque Nationale,” Langues orientales anciennes: philologique et linguistique 1 (1988): 111–113; Alin Suciu, “New Fragments of the Gospels in Fayyumic,” Alin Suciu: research on patristics, apocrypha, Coptic literature and manuscripts, December 7, 2011, http://alinsuciu.com/2011/12/07/new-fayyumic-fragments-of-the-gospels/.</p>
<p>Louvain fragment: Louis-Théophile Lefort, “Coptica Lovaniensia,” Le Muséon 51, no. 1 (1938): 3–5.</p>
